         <abstract id="aspace_092f6dad28aadd27bb031b503dbbfa24">The Engineering, Science, Management
            War Training (ESMWT) program trained students to participate in defense activities, in
            order to meet the shortage of engineers, chemists, physicists, and production
            supervisors during World War II. The Duke University ESMWT was administered by A. S.
            Brower, and was overseen by the United States Department of Education. The Engineering,
            Science, and Management War Training Program Records includes general information,
            forms, reports, bulletins, financial records, correspondence, and course material dating
            from 1940-1945. English.</abstract>
